This paper deals with the problem of online bin packing, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves packing rectangles, which is a geometric problem and falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the use of combinatorial techniques to prove the lower bound, which falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of online bin packing is also related to game theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC), as it involves analyzing the competitive ratio of algorithms.
